cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 115 miles ESE of Marathon, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: Moving NNW through the Florida Straits, forecast to cross the Florida Keys tonight–early Monday, then bend westward into the southeastern Gulf of Mexico and meander north-northwestward toward the eastern Gulf/Florida Big Bend late in the work-week.

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical Storm Watch in effect north of Englewood to Anna Maria Island (west coast Florida); no Atlantic-side watches near Jacksonville.
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical Storm Warning from Brevard/Volusia County line southward and around Keys; Hurricane Warning Keys; none near Jacksonville.
weather_observation.impacted_coast: South-central and southwest Florida coasts, Florida Keys, eventually portions of the eastern Gulf coast.
weather_observation.wind: Low (≤6% chance) of tropical-storm-force gusts; breezy 20–30 mph winds possible late Wednesday-Friday.
weather_observation.storm_surge: 1–2 ft of coastal inundation possible along the northeast Florida/Georgia coast during periods of onshore flow.
weather_observation.rainfall: Bands of rain could deliver 1–3 inches (locally 4 inches) Wednesday–Friday, leading to minor ponding in low-lying areas.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Dangerous rip currents and rough surf along area beaches beginning mid-week.
